'''''Fetichism in West Africa''''' is a book by [[the Reverend]] [[Robert Hamill Nassau]], a [[missionary]], published in 1904.

[[Image:Fetich Magician.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Fetich Magician with horns, wooden mask, spear, and sword, dress of leaves of palm and plantain. Frontispiece from ''Fetishism in West Africa: Forty Years' Observations of Native Customs and Superstitions''.
]]

The book relates the facts which Nassau discovered over the course of many years concerning traditional religions and the practice of [[Magic (paranormal)|sorcery]] in [[West Africa]] and how it related to the everyday lives of the people of that region.

