{{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | name = Ismael Blas Rolón Silvero, S.D.B. | title = [[Bishop]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Asunción|Archdiocese of Asuncion]] | image = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Roman Catholic Church]] | archdiocese = | diocese = | see = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Asunción|Archdiocese of Asuncion]] | term = 1970–1989 | predecessor = Juan Mena Porta | successor = Felipe Benitez Avalos <!-- Orders --> | ordination = November 23, 1941 | ordinated_by = | consecration = | consecrated_by = | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = {{birth date|1914|1|24}} | birth_place = [[Caazapá]], [[Paraguay]] [[Image:Flag of Paraguay.svg|25px]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2010|6|8|1914|1|24}} | death_place = | previous_post = Priest }}
'''Ismael Blas Rolón Silvero''' S.D.B. (January 24, 1914 – June 8, 2010) was a [[Paraguay]]an [[prelate]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]]. At the time of his death, he was one of the oldest Catholic bishops and the oldest bishop from Paraguay.
Rolón Silvero was born in [[Caazapá]], [[Paraguay]] in 1914. He was ordained a priest on November 23, 1941 from the [[religious institute]] of the [[Salesians of Don Bosco]]. He was appointed prelate to the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Caacupé|Caacupé Diocese]] on August 2, 1960. On October 20, 1965 he was appointed [[Titular Bishop]] of Furnos Maior and ordained January 23, 1966. Rolón Silvero was appointed bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Caacupé|Caacupé Diocese]] and then appointed to the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Asunción|Archdiocese of Asunción]] on June 16, 1970. Rolón retired from the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Asunción|Archdiocese of Asuncion]] on May 20, 1989.
