'''Mandrake of Oxford''' is a specialist independent publisher based in [[Oxford]], England,<ref>{{cite book | title = Directory of Publishing | author = [[The Publishers' Association]], [[Federation of European Publishers]] | year = 1991 | publisher = [[Orion Publishing Group|Cassell]] | location = New York | isbn = 0-304-32819-7 | pages = 99}}</ref> primarily known for the publication of "hands-on" books for occult practitioners.<ref name=evans1>Evans (2007), p. 39</ref> The company was started in 1986 under the name '''Golden Dawn Publications''',<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.weiserantiquarian.com/catalogtwo/ | title = Catalog # 2. | work = Weiser Antiquarian Books | access-date = 23 June 2007}}</ref> but changed its name to Mandrake upon the publication of ''Sexual Magick'' by Katon Shual (a pen-name of founder Mogg Morgan<ref>Evans (2007), p. 178</ref>) in 1988.<ref name=morgan> Mogg Morgan. [http://www.mandrake.uk.net/whoweare.htm Mandrake of Oxford: Who We Are] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070608041247/http://www.mandrake.uk.net/whoweare.htm |date=8 June 2007 }}</ref> Mandrake publishes texts on [[Magick (Aleister Crowley)|magick]], [[occult]]ure, [[tantra]] and [[Thelema]].<ref name=morgan/>

==Founder==
Mandrake's founder, Mogg Morgan, when interviewed by ''occultebooks'', said that he chose the name in 1987 as an homage to [[Aleister Crowley]] (see [[Mandrake Press]]) and that he prefers to publish new writers who are continuing to develop the [[Thelema|Thelemic]] tradition.<ref>Evans, Dave. [http://occultebooks.com/interviews/MoggMorganofMandrakePt1DE/tabid/75/Default.aspx Occult E-books meets Mogg Morgan of Mandrake] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070721034003/http://occultebooks.com/interviews/MoggMorganofMandrakePt1DE/tabid/75/Default.aspx |date=21 July 2007 }}</ref> Mandrake of Oxford is now a partnership of Mogg and Kym Morgan. Kym Morgan is mainly responsible for Mandrake's growing series of books on crime - "Classic Crime Studies".

==Publications==
